author: jplevyak
msg: TS-51: remove cruft: AUTO_PILOT_MODE, BSD_TCP, TRANSACTION_ON_A_THREAD
These are all experiments which produced no compelling benefit and have not
been touched in years.  Moreover performance landscape has changed. For example,
BSD_TCP was an experimental replacement of the Solaris TCP stack with the BSD
stack because of early inefficiencies in the Solaris stack which have long since
been dealt with.  Also remove some dead variables and duplicate interfaces.
